Edinburgh Street, Belmont Drive, Is Most Expensive in Scotland, Study Says

-- B y   T i m   F a r r a n d
-- 
2011-03-10T09:55:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-10/edinburgh-street-belmont-drive-is-most-expensive-in-scotland-study-says.html
Edinburgh’s Belmont Drive is the
most expensive residential street in  Scotland  with an average
house price of 2.346 million pounds ($3.8 million), according to
research from the Bank of Scotland, owned by the  Lloyds Banking
Group Plc. (LLOY)   A total 15 of the top 20 most expensive streets in Scotland
are in Edinburgh with Ettrick Road in Merchiston the second most
expensive followed by Dick Place in the Grange conservation
area, said the research published on Lloyds Banking Group’s
website.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Tim Farrand at 
 tfarrand@bloomberg.net  